A Communication Covenant is an agreement every member of a team makes about communicating: 
	·  	promising to communicate regularly (even when the news is bad),
	·  	promising to answer your email how many times a day,
	·  	agreeing that you will be using Google Docs for file management,
	·  	specifying when and where your meetings are (1-2 times a week),
	·  	promising to notify team mates if you can’t make a meeting,
	·  	agreeing to reasonable punishments if a team mate is late or misses without notifying everyone,
	·  	promising to volunteer to do things and to do them well and on time. 
	 
	Include a table of preferred email addresses and cell phone numbers.  Title the file TEAMNAMEContacts

If a teammate fails to contribute to the group assignments he/she will be confronted in a group meeting.  Under extreme measures, the issue will be brought to the instructor if his/her contribution level does not improve.
Gmail/GoogleDocs/Dropbox will be used as a repository for all emails, files, and notes relating to the group

If you are planning on missing the meeting, email or text the team at least 24 hours prior.
If you expect to be 5 minutes late or more, text at least one member of the team.
If you are more than 20 minutes late without prior notice to the meeting you need to bring snacks to the next meeting.

Email: Check at least twice a day
Response Time: 24 hours

Phone: Urgent matters 

Texting: At anytime for immediate response

Team members will equally distribute the work and provide constructive and timely feedback to each other. 
Team members will keep each other updated on their progress daily via email.

If a teammate fails to contribute to the group assignments he/she will be confronted in a group meeting.  Under extreme measures, the issue will be brought to the instructor if his/her contribution level does not improve.
